def min_coins(m, p):
        m.sort()
        p.sort()
        i = 0
        j = 0
        coins = 0
        while i < len(m) and j < len(p):
            if m[i] < p[j]:
                coins += m[i]
                i += 1
            else:
                coins += p[j]
                j += 1
        while i < len(m):
            coins += m[i]
            i += 1
        while j < len(p):
            coins += p[j]
            j += 1
        return coins

            m.append(m_i)

        print(min_coins(m, p))
